TELC:sample.name: XTAL
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Crystal clock count. Used as a reference count in converting many of the counters presented in this telemetry space.

TELC:sample.name: PACKAGE_CSTATE_BLOCK_REFCNT
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Reference count for block cause counters. Counts the number of 1ms intervals during which PkgC entry was blocked at least once by any reason. To calculate percent blocked by a specific reason, divide corresponding block reason counter by this counter value. Sums all prevent cause to PKGC

TELC:sample.name: PACKAGE_CSTATE_WAKE_REFCNT
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Candidate for removal. Reference count for wake cause counters. To calculate percent for each wake reason, divide by this number. Sums all wake cause from PKGC

TELC:sample.name: PREVENT_PKGC_DFX_OTHERS
TELC:sample.TELC:description: Sample, not counter.PKGC can be disabled using several methods e.g DFX, fuses, BIOS.Pcode will update this register with resolved disabled PKGC mask.Encoding: bit 0 set: disable C6.1. bit 1 set: disable C6.2. bit 2 is set: disable C10.1. bit 3 is set: disable C10.2. bit 4 is set: disable C10.3Lower 5 bits are being used, rest are reserved.More details in https://docs.intel.com/documents/pm_doc/src/lnl/HAS/PkgC/PkgC.html#resolving
